('w_body_B1_04','balance','/ˈbæləns/','noun','균형','The ability to stay steady and not fall.','She practiced {balance} by standing on one leg.','그녀는 한 발로 서서 균형 감각을 연습했어요.','balance','B1','body',1,'balance one leg stability practice yoga'),
('w_body_B1_05','injury','/ˈɪndʒəri/','noun','부상, 상처','Physical harm done to the body.','He got an {injury} during the football match.','그는 축구 경기 중에 부상을 당했어요.','injury','B1','body',1,'injury football sport bandage hurt'),
('w_body_B1_06','scar','/skɑː/','noun','흉터','A mark left on the skin after a wound has healed.','She has a small {scar} on her left knee.','그녀는 왼쪽 무릎에 작은 흉터가 있어요.','scar','B1','body',1,'scar knee skin healed mark'),
('w_body_B1_07','bruise','/bruːz/','noun','멍, 타박상','A mark on the skin caused by a blow or pressure.','He had a large {bruise} on his arm after the fall.','그는 넘어진 후 팔에 큰 멍이 들었어요.','bruise','B1','body',1,'bruise arm skin blue purple fall'),
('w_body_B1_08','sprain','/spreɪn/','noun','삐다, 염좌','An injury to a ligament caused by twisting a joint.','She had a {sprain} in her wrist from the accident.','그녀는 사고로 손목에 염좌가 생겼어요.','sprain','B1','body',1,'sprain wrist bandage joint injury'),
('w_body_B1_09','sweat','/swɛt/','noun','땀','Moisture that comes from the skin during heat or exercise.','{Sweat} dripped down his face during the run.','달리는 동안 그의 얼굴에 땀이 흘러내렸어요.','sweat','B1','body',1,'sweat run exercise drip face'),
('w_body_B1_10','pulse','/pʌls/','noun','맥박','The regular beating of the heart that can be felt in the wrist.','The nurse checked his {pulse} every hour.','간호사가 한 시간마다 그의 맥박을 확인했어요.','pulse','B1','body',1,'pulse wrist nurse check heartbeat'),
('w_body_B1_11','digest','/daɪˈdʒɛst/','verb','소화하다','To process food in the stomach and intestines.','The body takes time to {digest} heavy meals.','몸이 기름진 음식을 소화하는 데는 시간이 걸려요.','digest','B1','body',1,'digest stomach food body nutrition'),
('w_body_B1_12','circulation','/ˌsɜːkjʊˈleɪʃn/','noun','혈액 순환','The movement of blood through the body.','Exercise improves blood {circulation} throughout the body.','운동은 몸 전체의 혈액 순환을 개선시켜줘요.','circulation','B1','body',1,'circulation blood heart body flow'),
('w_body_B1_13','nervous system','/ˈnɜːvəs ˈsɪstəm/','noun','신경계','The network of nerves and cells that send signals through the body.','The {nervous system} controls everything from breathing to movement.','신경계는 호흡부터 움직임까지 모든 것을 조절해요.','nervous system','B1','body',1,'nervous system brain nerves diagram anatomy'),
('w_body_B1_14','immune system','/ɪˈmjuːn ˈsɪstəm/','noun','면역계','The body''s defence system against disease and infection.','A balanced diet supports a healthy {immune system}.','균형 잡힌 식단은 건강한 면역계를 지원해요.','immune system','B1','body',1,'immune system defense body health white blood'),
('w_body_B1_15','reflex','/ˈriːflɛks/','noun','반사 작용','An automatic movement or reaction to a stimulus.','Blinking is a natural {reflex} that protects the eye.','눈 깜박임은 눈을 보호하는 자연스러운 반사 작용이에요.','reflex','B1','body',1,'reflex blink eye automatic reaction body'),
('w_body_B1_16','sensation','/sɛnˈseɪʃn/','noun','감각, 느낌','A physical feeling or perception.','She felt a tingling {sensation} in her fingers.','그녀는 손가락에 저릿한 감각을 느꼈어요.','sensation','B1','body',1,'sensation tingling fingers nerve feeling'),
('w_body_B1_17','consciousness','/ˈkɒnʃəsnəs/','noun','의식','The state of being awake and aware of surroundings.','He slowly regained {consciousness} after the operation.','수술 후 그는 서서히 의식을 되찾았어요.','consciousness','B1','body',1,'consciousness awake aware hospital recovery'),
('w_body_B1_18','weight','/weɪt/','noun','체중, 무게','The heaviness of the body.','She monitors her {weight} with a scale every week.','그녀는 매주 체중계로 체중을 확인해요.','weight','B1','body',1,'weight scale body monitor weekly'),
('w_body_B1_19','height','/haɪt/','noun','키, 신장','The measurement from the bottom to the top of the body.','His {height} is 180 centimetres.','그의 키는 180센티미터예요.','height','B1','body',1,'height measuring tape wall child growth'),
('w_body_B1_20','shape','/ʃeɪp/','noun','체형, 모양','The physical form or outline of the body.','Regular exercise keeps the body in good {shape}.','규칙적인 운동은 몸을 좋은 체형으로 유지해줘요.','shape','B1','body',1,'shape body fitness exercise form'),
('w_body_B1_21','stretch','/strɛtʃ/','verb','늘이다, 스트레칭하다','To extend the body or a part of it fully.','Always {stretch} before running to avoid injury.','부상을 피하려면 달리기 전에 반드시 스트레칭하세요.','stretch','B1','body',1,'stretch morning yoga warm up body'),
('w_body_B1_22','tighten','/ˈtaɪtn/','verb','조이다, 긴장시키다','To make a muscle firm and contracted.','{Tighten} your core muscles when lifting.','물건을 들 때 복근을 긴장시키세요.','tighten','B1','body',1,'tighten core muscle lift gym workout'),
('w_body_B1_23','relax','/rɪˈlæks/','verb','긴장을 풀다, 이완하다','To make the body or muscles less tense.','Take a warm bath to {relax} your muscles.','따뜻한 목욕으로 근육을 이완하세요.','relax','B1','body',1,'relax bath warm muscle soothe'),
('w_body_B1_24','tense','/tɛns/','adjective','긴장된','Having the muscles stiff and tight.','Her shoulders were {tense} from working at the desk.','책상에서 일하느라 그녀의 어깨가 긴장되어 있었어요.','tense','B1','body',1,'tense shoulder desk work stiff'),
('w_body_B1_25','numb','/nʌm/','adjective','무감각한, 저린','Having no feeling or sensation.','Her fingers went {numb} in the cold.','추위에 그녀의 손가락이 저렸어요.','numb','B1','body',1,'numb fingers cold winter sensation'),
('w_body_B1_26','ache','/eɪk/','noun','(지속적인) 통증','A continuous dull pain in a part of the body.','He had a {headache} and a stomach {ache} all afternoon.','그는 오후 내내 두통과 복통이 있었어요.','ache','B1','body',1,'ache pain head stomach discomfort'),
('w_body_B1_27','sore','/sɔː/','adjective','아픈, 쓰라린','Painful and aching.','Her legs were {sore} after the long hike.','긴 하이킹 후에 그녀의 다리가 아팠어요.','sore','B1','body',1,'sore legs hiking pain muscles tired'),
('w_body_B1_28','relief','/rɪˈliːf/','noun','완화, 안도','The reduction or removal of pain or discomfort.','The medicine brought him great {relief}.','그 약은 그에게 큰 통증 완화를 가져다주었어요.','relief','B1','body',1,'relief medicine pain comfort sigh'),
('w_body_B1_29','recover','/rɪˈkʌvər/','verb','회복하다','To return to normal health after illness or injury.','It took him two weeks to {recover} from the cold.','감기에서 회복하는 데 2주가 걸렸어요.','recover','B1','body',1,'recover rest bed health illness'),
('w_body_B1_30','heal','/hiːl/','verb','낫다, 치유되다','To become healthy again after an injury or illness.','The wound will {heal} in about a week.','상처는 약 일주일 후에 나을 거예요.','heal','B1','body',1,'heal wound bandage skin recovery'),
('w_body_B1_31','faint','/feɪnt/','verb','기절하다, 실신하다','To suddenly lose consciousness for a short time.','She felt dizzy and nearly {fainted} in the heat.','그녀는 더위에 어지러워서 거의 기절할 뻔했어요.','fainted','B1','body',1,'faint dizzy heat unconscious floor'),
('w_body_B1_32','shiver','/ˈʃɪvər/','verb','떨다 (추위)','To shake slightly because of cold or fear.','He {shivered} in the cold night air.','그는 차가운 밤공기에 몸을 떨었어요.','shivered','B1','body',1,'shiver cold night air tremble body'),
('w_body_B1_33','tremble','/ˈtrɛmbl/','verb','떨다, 흔들리다','To shake involuntarily, often from fear or excitement.','Her hands {trembled} as she opened the letter.','그녀는 편지를 열면서 손이 떨렸어요.','trembled','B1','body',1,'tremble hands letter fear nervous'),
('w_body_B1_34','blush','/blʌʃ/','verb','얼굴이 붉어지다','To become red in the face because of embarrassment.','She {blushed} when he gave her the compliment.','그가 칭찬을 하자 그녀의 얼굴이 붉어졌어요.','blushed','B1','body',1,'blush cheeks red embarrassed compliment face'),
('w_body_B1_35','sneeze','/sniːz/','verb','재채기하다','To suddenly expel air through the nose and mouth.','He {sneezed} three times and reached for a tissue.','그는 세 번 재채기를 하고 휴지를 집었어요.','sneezed','B1','body',1,'sneeze tissue nose cold allergy'),
-- B2 (01–35)
('w_body_B2_01','metabolism','/mɪˈtæbəlɪzəm/','noun','신진대사','The chemical processes that occur in a living organism to sustain life.','A fast {metabolism} helps the body burn calories quickly.','빠른 신진대사는 몸이 칼로리를 빠르게 소모하는 데 도움이 돼요.','metabolism','B2','body',1,'metabolism energy burn calories body process'),
('w_body_B2_02','hormone','/ˈhɔːməʊn/','noun','호르몬','A chemical substance produced in the body that controls functions.','Stress can affect the balance of {hormones} in the body.','스트레스는 체내 호르몬 균형에 영향을 줄 수 있어요.','hormones','B2','body',1,'hormone chemical body balance stress gland'),
('w_body_B2_03','enzyme','/ˈɛnzaɪm/','noun','효소','A substance produced by the body that speeds up chemical reactions.','Digestive {enzymes} help break down food in the stomach.','소화 효소는 위에서 음식을 분해하는 것을 도와줘요.','enzymes','B2','body',1,'enzyme digestive food reaction chemical body'),
('w_body_B2_04','tissue','/ˈtɪʃuː/','noun','조직 (생물)','A group of cells that form a specific part of the body.','Scar {tissue} forms as a wound heals over time.','상처가 시간이 지나 아물면서 흉터 조직이 형성돼요.','tissue','B2','body',1,'tissue cell scar microscope biology'),
('w_body_B2_05','cell','/sɛl/','noun','세포','The smallest structural and functional unit of an organism.','The human body is made up of trillions of {cells}.','인체는 수조 개의 세포로 이루어져 있어요.','cells','B2','body',1,'cell microscope biology human body structure'),
('w_body_B2_06','oxygen','/ˈɒksɪdʒən/','noun','산소','A gas that all living organisms need to survive.','The lungs supply {oxygen} to the blood.','폐는 혈액에 산소를 공급해요.','oxygen','B2','body',1,'oxygen lungs breathing blood supply'),
('w_body_B2_07','blood vessel','/blʌd ˈvɛsl/','noun','혈관','A tube through which blood flows in the body.','High blood pressure can damage {blood vessels}.','고혈압은 혈관을 손상시킬 수 있어요.','blood vessels','B2','body',1,'blood vessel artery vein diagram anatomy'),
('w_body_B2_08','skeleton','/ˈskɛlɪtn/','noun','골격, 뼈대','The framework of bones supporting the body.','The human {skeleton} has 206 bones.','인체의 골격은 206개의 뼈로 이루어져 있어요.','skeleton','B2','body',1,'skeleton bones anatomy human 206 diagram'),
('w_body_B2_09','joint','/dʒɔɪnt/','noun','관절','A point where two bones meet and allow movement.','Arthritis causes pain in the {joints}.','관절염은 관절에 통증을 유발해요.','joints','B2','body',1,'joint knee anatomy arthritis movement bone'),
('w_body_B2_10','ligament','/ˈlɪɡəmənt/','noun','인대','A band of tissue connecting bones at a joint.','She tore a {ligament} in her knee during sport.','그녀는 운동 중 무릎 인대를 찢었어요.','ligament','B2','body',1,'ligament knee tear anatomy joint sport'),
('w_body_B2_11','tendon','/ˈtɛndən/','noun','힘줄','A cord of tissue connecting muscle to bone.','He injured his Achilles {tendon} while running.','그는 달리다가 아킬레스 힘줄을 다쳤어요.','tendon','B2','body',1,'tendon achilles anatomy muscle bone injury'),
('w_body_B2_12','cartilage','/ˈkɑːtɪlɪdʒ/','noun','연골','A firm but flexible tissue found in joints and the ear.','The knee is cushioned by {cartilage}.','무릎은 연골에 의해 완충되어 있어요.','cartilage','B2','body',1,'cartilage knee joint cushion anatomy'),
('w_body_B2_13','vein','/veɪn/','noun','정맥','A blood vessel that carries blood towards the heart.','You can see the blue {veins} on the inside of the wrist.','손목 안쪽에 파란 정맥이 보여요.','veins','B2','body',1,'vein wrist blue blood vessel anatomy'),
('w_body_B2_14','artery','/ˈɑːtəri/','noun','동맥','A blood vessel that carries blood away from the heart.','The carotid {artery} supplies blood to the brain.','경동맥은 뇌에 혈액을 공급해요.','artery','B2','body',1,'artery blood vessel heart anatomy diagram'),
('w_body_B2_15','lymph node','/lɪmf nəʊd/','noun','림프절','A small gland that filters lymph fluid and produces immune cells.','Swollen {lymph nodes} can be a sign of infection.','림프절이 부어오르는 것은 감염의 신호일 수 있어요.','lymph nodes','B2','body',1,'lymph node gland immune infection anatomy'),
('w_body_B2_16','antibody','/ˈæntɪbɒdi/','noun','항체','A protein produced by the immune system to fight infection.','Vaccines help the body produce {antibodies}.','백신은 몸이 항체를 생성하는 데 도움이 돼요.','antibodies','B2','body',1,'antibody immune system protein virus protection'),
('w_body_B2_17','inflammation','/ˌɪnfləˈmeɪʃn/','noun','염증','The body''s response to injury, causing redness and swelling.','Rest and ice can reduce {inflammation} in a joint.','휴식과 얼음찜질은 관절의 염증을 줄이는 데 도움이 돼요.','inflammation','B2','body',1,'inflammation swelling red joint injury ice'),
('w_body_B2_18','chronic','/ˈkrɒnɪk/','adjective','만성적인','Lasting for a long time or constantly recurring.','She has been living with {chronic} back pain for years.','그녀는 수년간 만성 허리 통증과 함께 살아왔어요.','chronic','B2','body',1,'chronic back pain long term health condition'),
('w_body_B2_19','acute','/əˈkjuːt/','adjective','급성의','Severe and occurring suddenly.','The patient had an {acute} reaction to the medication.','환자는 약물에 급성 반응을 보였어요.','acute','B2','body',1,'acute reaction medication hospital emergency'),
('w_body_B2_20','symptom','/ˈsɪmptəm/','noun','증상','A sign that indicates a disease or condition.','Fatigue is a common {symptom} of many illnesses.','피로는 많은 질병의 흔한 증상이에요.','symptom','B2','body',1,'symptom fatigue illness condition medical'),
('w_body_B2_21','diagnosis','/ˌdaɪəɡˈnəʊsɪs/','noun','진단','The process of identifying a disease from its signs and symptoms.','Early {diagnosis} improves the chances of recovery.','조기 진단은 회복 가능성을 높여줘요.','diagnosis','B2','body',1,'diagnosis doctor medical early detection health'),
('w_body_B2_22','anatomy','/əˈnætəmi/','noun','해부학, 해부 구조','The study of the structure of the body.','Students study {anatomy} to understand how the body works.','학생들은 신체가 어떻게 작동하는지 이해하려고 해부학을 공부해요.','anatomy','B2','body',1,'anatomy body chart study medical human'),
('w_body_B2_23','physiology','/ˌfɪziˈɒlədʒi/','noun','생리학','The branch of science concerned with how the body functions.','{Physiology} explains how organs work together.','생리학은 기관들이 어떻게 함께 작동하는지 설명해요.','physiology','B2','body',1,'physiology organs function science body'),
('w_body_B2_24','neuron','/ˈnjʊərɒn/','noun','뉴런, 신경 세포','A specialised cell that transmits nerve impulses.','{Neurons} send electrical signals through the nervous system.','뉴런은 신경계를 통해 전기 신호를 보내요.','neurons','B2','body',1,'neuron nerve cell brain signal biology'),
('w_body_B2_25','cortex','/ˈkɔːtɛks/','noun','대뇌 피질','The outer layer of the brain responsible for higher functions.','The prefrontal {cortex} is involved in decision making.','전전두엽 피질은 의사결정에 관여해요.','cortex','B2','body',1,'cortex brain prefrontal decision anatomy'),
('w_body_B2_26','gland','/ɡlænd/','noun','분비선, 샘','An organ that produces and releases substances for the body.','The thyroid {gland} regulates the body''s metabolism.','갑상선 분비선은 신체의 신진대사를 조절해요.','gland','B2','body',1,'gland thyroid metabolism hormone anatomy'),
('w_body_B2_27','organ','/ˈɔːɡən/','noun','장기, 기관','A part of the body with a specific vital function.','The heart is the most vital {organ} in the body.','심장은 신체에서 가장 중요한 장기예요.','organ','B2','body',1,'organ heart body vital anatomy medical'),
('w_body_B2_28','function','/ˈfʌŋkʃn/','noun','기능, 작용','The purpose or role of a body part or system.','The main {function} of the kidney is to filter blood.','신장의 주요 기능은 혈액을 걸러내는 것이에요.','function','B2','body',1,'function kidney filter blood anatomy role'),
('w_body_B2_29','structure','/ˈstrʌktʃər/','noun','구조, 구성','The arrangement of parts that form a body or organ.','The {structure} of DNA was discovered in 1953.','DNA의 구조는 1953년에 발견되었어요.','structure','B2','body',1,'structure DNA discovery science anatomy'),
('w_body_B2_30','abnormal','/æbˈnɔːml/','adjective','비정상적인','Different from what is typical or expected in the body.','The scan showed {abnormal} tissue growth.','스캔 결과 비정상적인 조직 증식이 보였어요.','abnormal','B2','body',1,'abnormal scan tissue medical result'),
('w_body_B2_31','degenerate','/dɪˈdʒɛnəreɪt/','verb','퇴화하다, 악화하다','To decline in quality or function over time.','Cartilage can {degenerate} as people age.','연골은 나이가 들면서 퇴화할 수 있어요.','degenerate','B2','body',1,'degenerate cartilage aging joint decay'),
('w_body_B2_32','regenerate','/rɪˈdʒɛnəreɪt/','verb','재생하다','To grow or produce again after damage.','Skin cells constantly {regenerate} themselves.','피부 세포는 지속적으로 자기 자신을 재생해요.','regenerate','B2','body',1,'regenerate skin cell renew biology healing'),
('w_body_B2_33','regulate','/ˈrɛɡjʊleɪt/','verb','조절하다','To control or maintain a biological process at the right level.','The brain {regulates} body temperature automatically.','뇌는 체온을 자동으로 조절해요.','regulates','B2','body',1,'regulate temperature brain body control'),
('w_body_B2_34','stimulate','/ˈstɪmjʊleɪt/','verb','자극하다','To make something more active or increase its response.','Exercise {stimulates} the release of endorphins.','운동은 엔도르핀 분비를 자극해요.','stimulates','B2','body',1,'stimulate exercise endorphin brain response'),
('w_body_B2_35','inhibit','/ɪnˈhɪbɪt/','verb','억제하다','To slow down or prevent a biological process.','Certain drugs {inhibit} the growth of bacteria.','특정 약물은 박테리아 성장을 억제해요.','inhibit','B2','body',1,'inhibit drug bacteria growth suppress'),
-- C1 (01–35)
('w_body_C1_01','autonomic nervous system','/ˌɔːtəˈnɒmɪk ˈnɜːvəs ˈsɪstəm/','noun','자율 신경계','The part of the nervous system that controls involuntary functions.','The {autonomic nervous system} regulates heart rate and digestion.','자율 신경계는 심박수와 소화를 조절해요.','autonomic nervous system','C1','body',1,'autonomic nervous system diagram brain involuntary'),
('w_body_C1_02','somatic','/səʊˈmætɪk/','adjective','신체의, 체세포의','Relating to the body as distinct from the mind.','{Somatic} therapy addresses physical tensions held in the body.','신체 치료는 몸에 축적된 신체적 긴장을 다루어요.','somatic','C1','body',1,'somatic body therapy tension physical mind'),
('w_body_C1_03','peripheral','/pəˈrɪfərəl/','adjective','말초의','Relating to the outer part of the body or nervous system.','The {peripheral} nervous system connects the brain to the limbs.','말초 신경계는 뇌와 사지를 연결해요.','peripheral','C1','body',1,'peripheral nervous system limbs connection anatomy'),
('w_body_C1_04','cardiovascular','/ˌkɑːdiəʊˈvæskjʊlər/','adjective','심혈관의','Relating to the heart and blood vessels.','{Cardiovascular} exercise improves heart health.','심혈관 운동은 심장 건강을 향상시켜요.','cardiovascular','C1','body',1,'cardiovascular heart exercise running health'),
('w_body_C1_05','respiratory','/rɪˈspɪrətri/','adjective','호흡기의','Relating to the organs and processes of breathing.','{Respiratory} infections can affect the lungs.','호흡기 감염은 폐에 영향을 줄 수 있어요.','respiratory','C1','body',1,'respiratory lungs breathing infection anatomy'),
('w_body_C1_06','endocrine','/ˈɛndəkrɪn/','adjective','내분비의','Relating to glands that secrete hormones directly into the blood.','The {endocrine} system controls many bodily functions through hormones.','내분비계는 호르몬을 통해 많은 신체 기능을 조절해요.','endocrine','C1','body',1,'endocrine hormone gland system anatomy'),
('w_body_C1_07','cerebral','/ˈsɛrɪbrəl/','adjective','대뇌의, 뇌의','Relating to the brain or cerebrum.','A {cerebral} stroke affects blood flow to the brain.','뇌졸중은 뇌로의 혈류에 영향을 미쳐요.','cerebral','C1','body',1,'cerebral brain stroke anatomy cortex'),
('w_body_C1_08','pulmonary','/ˈpʌlmənəri/','adjective','폐의','Relating to the lungs.','{Pulmonary} embolism is a potentially life-threatening blockage.','폐색전증은 잠재적으로 생명을 위협하는 폐색이에요.','pulmonary','C1','body',1,'pulmonary lung embolism anatomy medical'),
('w_body_C1_09','homeostasis','/ˌhəʊmiəʊˈsteɪsɪs/','noun','항상성','The process by which the body maintains a stable internal environment.','The body maintains {homeostasis} by regulating temperature and pH.','신체는 체온과 pH를 조절함으로써 항상성을 유지해요.','homeostasis','C1','body',1,'homeostasis balance internal body temperature'),
('w_body_C1_10','proprioception','/ˌprəʊpriəˈsɛpʃn/','noun','고유감각','The sense of the position and movement of one''s own body.','Dancers rely on {proprioception} to move with precision.','무용수들은 정확하게 움직이기 위해 고유감각에 의존해요.','proprioception','C1','body',1,'proprioception balance dance movement body sense'),
('w_body_C1_11','vestibular','/vɛˈstɪbjʊlər/','adjective','전정의','Relating to the vestibule of the inner ear and sense of balance.','The {vestibular} system helps maintain equilibrium.','전정계는 균형 유지를 도와줘요.','vestibular','C1','body',1,'vestibular inner ear balance equilibrium anatomy'),
('w_body_C1_12','nociception','/ˌnəʊsɪˈsɛpʃn/','noun','침해수용, 통각','The process of perceiving potentially harmful stimuli as pain.','{Nociception} alerts the body to tissue damage.','침해수용은 신체에 조직 손상을 알려줘요.','nociception','C1','body',1,'nociception pain signal tissue nerve receptor'),
('w_body_C1_13','proprioceptive','/ˌprəʊpriəˈsɛptɪv/','adjective','고유감각의','Relating to the internal sense of body position and movement.','{Proprioceptive} training improves balance in athletes.','고유감각 훈련은 운동선수의 균형을 향상시켜요.','proprioceptive','C1','body',1,'proprioceptive training athlete balance stability'),
('w_body_C1_14','synaptic','/sɪˈnæptɪk/','adjective','시냅스의','Relating to the junction between nerve cells.','{Synaptic} connections form the basis of memory.','시냅스 연결은 기억의 기반을 형성해요.','synaptic','C1','body',1,'synaptic neuron connection memory brain signal'),
('w_body_C1_15','dendrite','/ˈdɛndraɪt/','noun','수상돌기','A short branching extension of a nerve cell that receives signals.','{Dendrites} receive electrical signals from other neurons.','수상돌기는 다른 뉴런에서 전기 신호를 받아요.','dendrites','C1','body',1,'dendrite neuron signal branch anatomy brain'),
('w_body_C1_16','axon','/ˈæksɒn/','noun','축삭돌기','The long thread-like part of a nerve cell that transmits signals.','The {axon} carries impulses away from the cell body.','축삭돌기는 세포체에서 자극을 멀리 전달해요.','axon','C1','body',1,'axon neuron signal transmit anatomy'),
('w_body_C1_17','motor neuron','/ˈməʊtər ˈnjʊərɒn/','noun','운동 뉴런','A nerve cell that transmits signals from the brain to muscles.','{Motor neurons} enable voluntary movement of the body.','운동 뉴런은 신체의 수의 운동을 가능하게 해요.','motor neurons','C1','body',1,'motor neuron brain muscle movement signal'),
('w_body_C1_18','sensory','/ˈsɛnsəri/','adjective','감각의','Relating to the senses or sensation.','{Sensory} nerves carry information from the body to the brain.','감각 신경은 신체에서 뇌로 정보를 전달해요.','sensory','C1','body',1,'sensory nerve brain body information signal'),
('w_body_C1_19','reflex arc','/ˈriːflɛks ɑːk/','noun','반사호','The neural pathway that controls a reflex action.','A {reflex arc} allows fast responses without brain involvement.','반사호는 뇌의 개입 없이 빠른 반응을 가능하게 해요.','reflex arc','C1','body',1,'reflex arc neural pathway spine reaction fast'),
('w_body_C1_20','epithelial','/ˌɛpɪˈθiːliəl/','adjective','상피의','Relating to the thin layer of tissue lining body surfaces.','{Epithelial} cells line the inside of the digestive tract.','상피 세포는 소화관 안쪽을 덮고 있어요.','epithelial','C1','body',1,'epithelial cell tissue lining surface anatomy'),
('w_body_C1_21','adipose','/ˈædɪpəʊs/','adjective','지방의, 지방 조직의','Relating to fat tissue stored in the body.','{Adipose} tissue insulates the body and stores energy.','지방 조직은 몸을 보온하고 에너지를 저장해요.','adipose','C1','body',1,'adipose fat tissue energy insulation body'),
('w_body_C1_22','connective tissue','/kəˈnɛktɪv ˈtɪʃuː/','noun','결합 조직','Tissue that supports and connects other tissues in the body.','{Connective tissue} holds organs in place throughout the body.','결합 조직은 신체 전반에서 장기를 제자리에 고정시켜요.','connective tissue','C1','body',1,'connective tissue support structure anatomy organs'),
('w_body_C1_23','skeletal','/ˈskɛlɪtl/','adjective','골격의','Relating to the skeleton or bones of the body.','{Skeletal} muscles are attached to bones and move the body.','골격근은 뼈에 붙어 있고 몸을 움직이게 해요.','skeletal','C1','body',1,'skeletal muscle bone anatomy body movement'),
('w_body_C1_24','smooth muscle','/smuːð ˈmʌsl/','noun','평활근','Involuntary muscle found in the walls of internal organs.','{Smooth muscle} controls the movement of food in the gut.','평활근은 장에서 음식의 움직임을 조절해요.','smooth muscle','C1','body',1,'smooth muscle gut involuntary organ anatomy'),
('w_body_C1_25','cardiac muscle','/ˈkɑːdiæk ˈmʌsl/','noun','심근','The involuntary muscle that forms the wall of the heart.','{Cardiac muscle} beats continuously without tiring.','심근은 지치지 않고 계속해서 박동해요.','cardiac muscle','C1','body',1,'cardiac muscle heart beat anatomy involuntary'),
('w_body_C1_26','thalamus','/ˈθæləməs/','noun','시상','A part of the brain that relays sensory signals to the cortex.','The {thalamus} acts as a relay station for sensory information.','시상은 감각 정보를 위한 중계 기지 역할을 해요.','thalamus','C1','body',1,'thalamus brain relay sensory anatomy structure'),
('w_body_C1_27','hypothalamus','/ˌhaɪpəʊˈθæləməs/','noun','시상하부','A region of the brain that controls body temperature and hormones.','The {hypothalamus} regulates hunger, thirst, and temperature.','시상하부는 배고픔, 갈증, 체온을 조절해요.','hypothalamus','C1','body',1,'hypothalamus brain hunger temperature hormone control'),
('w_body_C1_28','amygdala','/əˈmɪɡdələ/','noun','편도체','A brain structure involved in processing emotions, especially fear.','The {amygdala} plays a key role in the fear response.','편도체는 공포 반응에서 핵심적인 역할을 해요.','amygdala','C1','body',1,'amygdala brain fear emotion response anatomy'),
('w_body_C1_29','hippocampus','/ˌhɪpəˈkæmpəs/','noun','해마 (뇌)','A brain region essential for forming new memories.','The {hippocampus} is crucial for long-term memory formation.','해마는 장기 기억 형성에 매우 중요해요.','hippocampus','C1','body',1,'hippocampus brain memory anatomy formation'),
('w_body_C1_30','prefrontal cortex','/ˌpriːˈfrʌntl ˈkɔːtɛks/','noun','전전두엽 피질','The front part of the brain that controls decision-making and behaviour.','The {prefrontal cortex} helps regulate impulsive behaviour.','전전두엽 피질은 충동적인 행동을 조절하는 데 도움이 돼요.','prefrontal cortex','C1','body',1,'prefrontal cortex brain decision impulse anatomy'),
('w_body_C1_31','neurological','/ˌnjʊərəˈlɒdʒɪkl/','adjective','신경학적인','Relating to the nervous system and its disorders.','{Neurological} symptoms can include memory loss and tremors.','신경학적 증상에는 기억 상실과 떨림이 포함될 수 있어요.','neurological','C1','body',1,'neurological symptom brain nervous system disorder'),
('w_body_C1_32','gastrointestinal','/ˌɡæstrəʊɪnˈtɛstɪnl/','adjective','위장의, 위장관의','Relating to the stomach and intestines.','{Gastrointestinal} problems include bloating and acid reflux.','위장 문제에는 복부팽만과 위산 역류가 포함돼요.','gastrointestinal','C1','body',1,'gastrointestinal stomach intestine anatomy digestion'),
('w_body_C1_33','musculoskeletal','/ˌmʌskjʊləʊˈskɛlɪtl/','adjective','근골격의','Relating to both the muscles and the skeleton.','{Musculoskeletal} disorders affect joints and muscles together.','근골격계 질환은 관절과 근육 모두에 영향을 미쳐요.','musculoskeletal','C1','body',1,'musculoskeletal muscle bone joint anatomy disorder'),
('w_body_C1_34','biomechanics','/ˌbaɪəʊmɪˈkænɪks/','noun','생체역학','The study of mechanical principles applied to living bodies.','{Biomechanics} helps athletes improve their movement efficiency.','생체역학은 운동선수들이 움직임 효율성을 높이는 데 도움이 돼요.','biomechanics','C1','body',1,'biomechanics athlete movement efficiency study'),
('w_body_C1_35','kinaesthesia','/ˌkɪnɪsˈθiːziə/','noun','운동감각','The sense of the movement and position of body parts.','{Kinaesthesia} allows you to type without looking at your hands.','운동감각 덕분에 손을 보지 않고도 타이핑할 수 있어요.','kinaesthesia','C1','body',1,'kinaesthesia typing sense movement body position'),
-- C2 (01–35)
('w_body_C2_01','epigenetics','/ˌɛpɪdʒɪˈnɛtɪks/','noun','후성유전학','The study of changes in gene expression not caused by DNA changes.','{Epigenetics} shows how environment can alter gene activity.','후성유전학은 환경이 유전자 활성을 어떻게 바꿀 수 있는지 보여줘요.','epigenetics','C2','body',1,'epigenetics gene expression DNA environment research'),
('w_body_C2_02','neuroplasticity','/ˌnjʊərəʊplæˈstɪsɪti/','noun','신경 가소성','The brain''s ability to reorganise itself by forming new connections.','Learning a language promotes {neuroplasticity} in adults.','언어를 배우는 것은 성인의 신경 가소성을 촉진해요.','neuroplasticity','C2','body',1,'neuroplasticity brain learning connections neurons adapt'),
('w_body_C2_03','phenotype','/ˈfiːnətaɪp/','noun','표현형','The observable characteristics of an organism from genes and environment.','Eye colour is an example of a visible {phenotype}.','눈 색깔은 눈에 보이는 표현형의 예예요.','phenotype','C2','body',1,'phenotype gene expression trait biology eye color'),
('w_body_C2_04','genotype','/ˈdʒiːnətaɪp/','noun','유전자형','The genetic composition of an organism.','Your {genotype} influences but does not completely determine health.','유전자형은 건강에 영향을 주지만 완전히 결정하지는 않아요.','genotype','C2','body',1,'genotype DNA genetics heredity biology'),
('w_body_C2_05','ontogenesis','/ˌɒntəˈdʒɛnɪsɪs/','noun','개체 발생','The development of an individual organism from embryo to adult.','{Ontogenesis} involves complex genetic and environmental interactions.','개체 발생은 복잡한 유전적·환경적 상호작용을 수반해요.','ontogenesis','C2','body',1,'ontogenesis development embryo growth biology'),
('w_body_C2_06','immunomodulation','/ɪˌmjuːnəʊˌmɒdjʊˈleɪʃn/','noun','면역 조절','The adjustment of the immune response by a drug or agent.','Some foods support {immunomodulation} and reduce inflammation.','일부 식품은 면역 조절을 지원하고 염증을 줄여줘요.','immunomodulation','C2','body',1,'immunomodulation immune response adjust inflammation food'),
('w_body_C2_07','synaptic plasticity','/sɪˈnæptɪk plæˈstɪsɪti/','noun','시냅스 가소성','The ability of synapses to strengthen or weaken over time.','{Synaptic plasticity} is fundamental to learning and memory.','시냅스 가소성은 학습과 기억의 근본이에요.','synaptic plasticity','C2','body',1,'synaptic plasticity learning memory brain neuron'),
('w_body_C2_08','neurogenesis','/ˌnjʊərəˈdʒɛnɪsɪs/','noun','신경 발생','The process of generating new neurons in the brain.','Exercise has been shown to promote {neurogenesis} in the hippocampus.','운동은 해마에서 신경 발생을 촉진하는 것으로 알려져 있어요.','neurogenesis','C2','body',1,'neurogenesis neuron brain hippocampus exercise'),
('w_body_C2_09','apoptosis','/ˌæpəˈtəʊsɪs/','noun','세포 자연사','The process of programmed cell death in living organisms.','{Apoptosis} removes damaged cells to maintain healthy tissue.','세포 자연사는 손상된 세포를 제거하여 건강한 조직을 유지해요.','apoptosis','C2','body',1,'apoptosis cell death programmed biology tissue'),
('w_body_C2_10','homeostatic regulation','/ˌhəʊmiəʊˈstætɪk ˌrɛɡjʊˈleɪʃn/','noun','항상성 조절','The mechanisms that maintain stable conditions inside the body.','{Homeostatic regulation} keeps blood sugar within a safe range.','항상성 조절은 혈당을 안전한 범위 내로 유지해줘요.','homeostatic regulation','C2','body',1,'homeostatic regulation blood sugar balance internal body'),
('w_body_C2_11','myelination','/ˌmaɪəlɪˈneɪʃn/','noun','수초화','The process of forming a myelin sheath around nerve fibres.','{Myelination} speeds up electrical transmission along axons.','수초화는 축삭을 따라 전기 전달 속도를 높여줘요.','myelination','C2','body',1,'myelination myelin axon nerve speed transmission'),
('w_body_C2_12','neurodegeneration','/ˌnjʊərəʊdɪˌdʒɛnəˈreɪʃn/','noun','신경 퇴행','The progressive loss of structure or function of neurons.','Alzheimer''s disease involves {neurodegeneration} of brain cells.','알츠하이머병은 뇌 세포의 신경 퇴행을 수반해요.','neurodegeneration','C2','body',1,'neurodegeneration alzheimer brain cell loss'),
('w_body_C2_13','somatic mutation','/səʊˈmætɪk mjuːˈteɪʃn/','noun','체세포 돌연변이','A genetic change occurring in a body cell that is not inherited.','A {somatic mutation} in a skin cell can lead to skin cancer.','피부 세포의 체세포 돌연변이는 피부암으로 이어질 수 있어요.','somatic mutation','C2','body',1,'somatic mutation gene skin cancer cell DNA'),
('w_body_C2_14','mitosis','/maɪˈtəʊsɪs/','noun','유사분열','The process of cell division resulting in two identical daughter cells.','{Mitosis} allows the body to grow and replace damaged cells.','유사분열은 몸이 성장하고 손상된 세포를 교체할 수 있게 해줘요.','mitosis','C2','body',1,'mitosis cell division growth replace biology'),
('w_body_C2_15','meiosis','/maɪˈəʊsɪs/','noun','감수분열','Cell division that produces reproductive cells with half the chromosomes.','{Meiosis} produces sperm and egg cells for reproduction.','감수분열은 생식을 위한 정자와 난자를 생성해요.','meiosis','C2','body',1,'meiosis cell division reproduction chromosome biology'),
('w_body_C2_16','genome','/ˈdʒiːnəʊm/','noun','게놈, 유전체','The complete set of genetic material in an organism.','Scientists have mapped the entire human {genome}.','과학자들은 전체 인간 게놈을 지도화했어요.','genome','C2','body',1,'genome DNA mapping human genetics science'),
('w_body_C2_17','chromosomal','/ˌkrəʊməˈsəʊml/','adjective','염색체의','Relating to chromosomes and their structure or number.','Some conditions are caused by {chromosomal} abnormalities.','일부 질환은 염색체 이상으로 인해 발생해요.','chromosomal','C2','body',1,'chromosomal abnormality condition DNA genetics'),
('w_body_C2_18','DNA methylation','/ˌdiːɛnˈeɪ ˌmɛθɪˈleɪʃn/','noun','DNA 메틸화','A chemical process that regulates gene expression in cells.','{DNA methylation} can silence genes without changing their sequence.','DNA 메틸화는 유전자 서열을 바꾸지 않고도 유전자를 침묵시킬 수 있어요.','DNA methylation','C2','body',1,'DNA methylation gene regulation epigenetics cell'),
('w_body_C2_19','telomere','/ˈtɛləmɪər/','noun','텔로미어','A protective cap at the end of a chromosome that shortens with age.','Short {telomeres} are associated with cellular ageing.','짧은 텔로미어는 세포 노화와 관련이 있어요.','telomeres','C2','body',1,'telomere chromosome aging cell cap DNA'),
('w_body_C2_20','stem cell','/stɛm sɛl/','noun','줄기세포','An undifferentiated cell that can develop into many types of cells.','{Stem cell} therapy shows promise for treating tissue damage.','줄기세포 치료는 조직 손상 치료에 가능성을 보여줘요.','stem cell','C2','body',1,'stem cell therapy regeneration tissue biology'),
('w_body_C2_21','cytokine','/ˈsaɪtəkɪn/','noun','사이토카인','A small protein that signals between cells in the immune system.','{Cytokines} coordinate the body''s response to infection.','사이토카인은 감염에 대한 신체의 반응을 조율해요.','cytokines','C2','body',1,'cytokine immune signal protein infection coordination'),
('w_body_C2_22','neurotransmitter','/ˌnjʊərəʊtrænsˈmɪtər/','noun','신경전달물질','A chemical that transmits signals between neurons.','Dopamine is a key {neurotransmitter} involved in reward.','도파민은 보상에 관여하는 핵심 신경전달물질이에요.','neurotransmitter','C2','body',1,'neurotransmitter dopamine brain signal reward chemical'),
('w_body_C2_23','serotonin','/ˌsɛrəˈtəʊnɪn/','noun','세로토닌','A neurotransmitter that contributes to feelings of well-being and happiness.','Exercise boosts {serotonin} levels and improves mood.','운동은 세로토닌 수치를 높이고 기분을 개선해줘요.','serotonin','C2','body',1,'serotonin mood happiness brain exercise chemical'),
('w_body_C2_24','dopamine','/ˈdəʊpəmiːn/','noun','도파민','A neurotransmitter linked to pleasure and motivation.','Achieving goals triggers a release of {dopamine} in the brain.','목표를 달성하면 뇌에서 도파민이 분비돼요.','dopamine','C2','body',1,'dopamine reward brain motivation goal achievement'),
('w_body_C2_25','cortisol','/ˈkɔːtɪsɒl/','noun','코르티솔','A steroid hormone released in response to stress.','High {cortisol} levels over time can impair immune function.','장기간 높은 코르티솔 수치는 면역 기능을 저하시킬 수 있어요.','cortisol','C2','body',1,'cortisol stress hormone immune adrenal'),
('w_body_C2_26','oxytocin','/ˌɒksɪˈtəʊsɪn/','noun','옥시토신','A hormone that promotes bonding, trust, and social connection.','{Oxytocin} is released when you hug someone you love.','사랑하는 사람을 안을 때 옥시토신이 분비돼요.','oxytocin','C2','body',1,'oxytocin hug bonding love hormone trust'),
('w_body_C2_27','endorphin','/ɛnˈdɔːfɪn/','noun','엔도르핀','A hormone that relieves pain and produces feelings of pleasure.','Running releases {endorphins} that create a sense of euphoria.','달리기는 행복감을 만들어내는 엔도르핀을 분비시켜요.','endorphins','C2','body',1,'endorphin running exercise euphoria pain relief'),
('w_body_C2_28','proprioceptive feedback','/ˌprəʊpriəˈsɛptɪv ˈfiːdbæk/','noun','고유감각 피드백','Sensory information from muscles and joints about body position.','{Proprioceptive feedback} helps the body adjust balance in real time.','고유감각 피드백은 신체가 실시간으로 균형을 조정하는 데 도움이 돼요.','proprioceptive feedback','C2','body',1,'proprioceptive feedback balance body position muscle'),
('w_body_C2_29','somatosensory','/ˌsəʊmætəˈsɛnsəri/','adjective','체감각의','Relating to the sensations of the body such as touch and pain.','The {somatosensory} cortex processes touch and temperature signals.','체감각 피질은 촉감과 온도 신호를 처리해요.','somatosensory','C2','body',1,'somatosensory cortex touch temperature brain signal'),
('w_body_C2_30','interoception','/ˌɪntərəˈsɛpʃn/','noun','내수용 감각','The sense of the internal state of one''s own body.','{Interoception} helps regulate emotions by sensing internal signals.','내수용 감각은 내부 신호를 감지하여 감정 조절을 도와줘요.','interoception','C2','body',1,'interoception internal body sense emotion regulate'),
('w_body_C2_31','nociceptor','/ˌnəʊsɪˈsɛptər/','noun','침해수용기','A sensory receptor that detects potentially harmful stimuli.','{Nociceptors} in the skin detect heat and mechanical pressure.','피부의 침해수용기는 열과 기계적 압력을 감지해요.','nociceptors','C2','body',1,'nociceptor skin pain heat pressure receptor'),
('w_body_C2_32','mechanoreceptor','/ˌmɛkənəʊrɪˈsɛptər/','noun','기계수용기','A sensory cell that responds to mechanical pressure or distortion.','{Mechanoreceptors} in the fingertips are sensitive to texture.','손끝의 기계수용기는 질감에 민감해요.','mechanoreceptors','C2','body',1,'mechanoreceptor fingertip touch texture skin sense'),
('w_body_C2_33','thermoreceptor','/ˌθɜːməʊrɪˈsɛptər/','noun','열수용기','A sensory receptor that detects changes in temperature.','{Thermoreceptors} in the skin respond to both heat and cold.','피부의 열수용기는 열과 차가움 모두에 반응해요.','thermoreceptors','C2','body',1,'thermoreceptor skin temperature cold heat sense'),
('w_body_C2_34','chemoreceptor','/ˌkiːməʊrɪˈsɛptər/','noun','화학수용기','A sensory receptor that detects chemical stimuli such as taste or smell.','{Chemoreceptors} in the nose detect odour molecules.','코의 화학수용기는 냄새 분자를 감지해요.','chemoreceptors','C2','body',1,'chemoreceptor nose smell odour chemical sense'),
('w_body_C2_35','vestibulo-ocular','/vɛˈstɪbjʊləʊ ˈɒkjʊlər/','adjective','전정-안구의','Relating to the reflex that stabilises vision during head movement.','The {vestibulo-ocular} reflex keeps vision stable when you move your head.','전정-안구 반사는 머리를 움직일 때 시야를 안정적으로 유지해줘요.','vestibulo-ocular','C2','body',1,'vestibulo-ocular reflex balance vision head movement')
ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;
